value.value: A sigilla on the lateral of sternum, where an extension of the endosternite attaches.

label.value: base of gland spigot of posterior median spinneret

value.value: The base of a gland spigot on the posterior median spinneret.

label.value: shaft of gland spigot of posterior median spinneret

value.value: The shaft of a gland spigot on the posterior median spinneret.
The base of the aggregate gland spigot.
The shaft of the aggregate gland spigot.
A superior claw on leg 1.
A small horizontal sclerite on the pleural area that may occur between two coxae.
Each of the small horizontal sclerites on the pleural area, between the coxae and the carapace.
A cusple on the endites of some Mygalomorphae.
The sigilla on the dorsum of the opisthosoma, where a dorso-ventral opisthosomal muscle inserts.
A hygroreceptor and thermosensory organ situated on the dorsal side of the leg and palpal tarsi.
A group of tenent setae covering surfaces on appendages. Do not confuse with the generic use as a brush of unspecified setae.

A paired cluster of tenent setae on the feet of many vagrant spiders, which may arise from a patch solidly integrated with the surrounding cuticle or may be inserted on an articulate plate (the claw tuft plate).

A sensory seta on the dorsal surfaces of legs and palps, specialized in detecting air movement. The setal shaft is slender, perpendicular to the cuticle surface, usually curved backwards and longer than the neighboring setae. Trichobothria are typically disposed in longitudinal series of distally increasing length.
A superior claw on leg 2.

A large articulated seta, with thick and long shaft and robust socket. Macrosetae are inervated by three neurons and become erected when the hemolymph pressure increases. Nerve impulses are generated only during the erection phase. They occur mainly on appendages, but sometimes similar setae occur on the opisthosoma as well.
A process on the retrolateral margin of the cymbium, midway between the base and the tip.
A structure made of silk fibers or glue.
A silk cable of major ampullate fibers.
The sticky line composed by dry axial fibers and a viscous glue as in the araneoid spiral.
A female gamete where meiosis has progressed to metaphase II and is able to participate in fertilization.
The spiracle of the anterior booklung.
The gland on the chelicera or carapace that produced the venom injected through the fang.
A superior claw on leg 3.
A superior claw on leg 4.
Appendage of prosoma, between the chelicerae and leg I.

An eye where the retina receives the light indirectly, reflected by the tapetum. Indirect eyes usually appear shiny. Most commonly all eyes except the anterior medians are indirect, but the tapetum is lost in several families, such as Salticidae. Philodromidae and Eresidae.
A generic term for pre-hatching stages.
Very short macroseta, often with a blunt tip.
The socket of the trichobothria.
The shaft of the trichobothria.
The socket of the macroseta.
A gland located in the tibia of leg 1.

definition.value: The tibial gland was reported in e.g., Leptonetidae (Platnick 1986).

value.value: The dorsal sclerite corresponding to a segment in the opisthosoma.
The ventral sclerite corresponding to a segment in the opisthosoma.
A specialized seta of some Theraphosidae spiders, with a basal breakage zone. The detached setae are transported by air or by contact and urticate the mammal skin.
Each of the small spigots on the posterior spinnerets. They extrude thin fibrils used to cover surfaces, such as the wrapping of preys, lining of silken cells, some layers in eggsacs.
A spigot found in some Mygalomorphae, with a globose base with striae, as in a pumpkin.
Each of the large spigots on the posterior spinnerets, occurring only in adult females. They extrude a silk used for some layers of the eggsac, probably used to regulate humidity.
A large spigot on the anterior lateral of posterior median spinnerets, extruding resistant fibers.
Each of the spigots on the posterior spinnerets of some cribellate spiders, with a shaft similar to those of cribellar spigots, strobilate except in Filistatidae.
The shaft of a scopular seta.
Any of the four appendages of prosoma, behind the palp.
The basal, 1st segment of the leg. It articulates with the trochanter through a prolateral ball-socket articulation.
Second segment of the leg, between the coxa and femur. It articulates with the femur through a pair of lateral condyles.
The 3rd segment of the leg, between trochanter and patella. It articulates with the patella through a pair of dorsal-lateral condyles.
The 4th segment of the leg, between femur and tibia. It articulates with the tibia through a medial dorsal condyle.
The 5th segment of the leg, between patella and metatarsus. It articulates with the metatarsus through a pair of dorsal-lateral condyles.
The 6th segment of the leg, between tibia and tarsus. It articulates with the tarsus through free joint without condyles.
The 7th segment of the leg, between the metatarsus and the pretarsus. It articulates with the pretarsus through a pair of lateral condyles.
